app.title: Supplementary Materials
app.p: The following are available online, Figure S1: HPLC chromatograms of the compound 5-containing mixture; Figure S2–S9: NMR spectra of the separated compounds; Figure S10: Fluorescein fluorescence decay cures induced by AAPH in the presence of Trolox or the separated compounds; Table S1: Partition coefficients ( K upper/lower) of compounds 1–10 from the 70% methanol extract of Muehlenbeckia volcanica (Benth.) Endl. at a serious of n-hexane/ethyl acetate/methanol/ n-butanol/water solvent systems; Table S2: Structural assignment of the separated compounds from the 70% methanol extract of Muehlenbeckia volcanica Meisn. using NMR, MS, and UV analysis; Table S3: Calibration cures of DPPH and ABTS radical inhibition (%) or AUC value by Trolox.
